  "description": [
    "flHLD APaiM Fvik nf the Svstem Vividly Set Forth in Photographic Displays Legislation Now in Force and Legislation Which Is NeededInteresting Facts About Child Labor and What It Does for the Child The Vicious Circle Exorbitant inch cost of child labor holding two million children in the United States in its thraldom and endangering the ltizenship of the future is vividly and pathetically told in an exhibit that recently left Washington to be featured at the PanamaPacific exposition This exhibit was an outstanding illustration of the work being done by the 8300 men and women united in the national child labor committee which closed its eleventh annual conrerence here a few weeks ago It contains more than 5000 tragic pictures of six to sixteen year old children dragging their wan little bodies to work eleven or more hours a day in the mills out In the bitter cold of the winters morning ill clad hopeless literally earning their bread in the sweat of their brows oftentimes crippled and maimed for life It took Lewis W Hine staff photographer for the national committee more than ten years to collect this pathetic display of human waste This exhibit divides the reasons why"
